  "texts": [
    "We simulated a fixed amount of blood (4000 particles) through PBF and added suction force to each particle within a suction range to simulate the effect of suction.",
    "Particles that are suctioned close enough to the suction tool will be removed and marked as inactive.",
    "To introduce randomness in the shape of the tissue, Bezier surfaces with random control points were used to generate random shapes.",
    "The Bezier surfaces are represented byS(u, v) = n i=0 m j=0 P i,j • B n,i (u) • B m,j (v), 0 ≤ u, v ≤ 1 (1)where P i,j are the control points, and B n,i (u) and B m,j (v) are the Bernstein basis functions defined byB n,i (x) = n! i!",
    "• x i • (1 -x) n-i."
  ],
